{"componentChunkName":"component---src-templates-lesson-template-js","path":"/intro","result":{"data":{"markdownRemark":{"html":"<h2 id=\"workshop-objective\" style=\"position:relative;\"><a href=\"#workshop-objective\" aria-label=\"workshop objective permalink\" class=\"anchor before\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" focusable=\"false\" height=\"16\" version=\"1.1\" viewBox=\"0 0 16 16\" width=\"16\"><path fill-rule=\"evenodd\" d=\"M4 9h1v1H4c-1.5 0-3-1.69-3-3.5S2.55 3 4 3h4c1.45 0 3 1.69 3 3.5 0 1.41-.91 2.72-2 3.25V8.59c.58-.45 1-1.27 1-2.09C10 5.22 8.98 4 8 4H4c-.98 0-2 1.22-2 2.5S3 9 4 9zm9-3h-1v1h1c1 0 2 1.22 2 2.5S13.98 12 13 12H9c-.98 0-2-1.22-2-2.5 0-.83.42-1.64 1-2.09V6.25c-1.09.53-2 1.84-2 3.25C6 11.31 7.55 13 9 13h4c1.45 0 3-1.69 3-3.5S14.5 6 13 6z\"></path></svg></a>Workshop Objective</h2>\n<p>Hello and welcome to the workshop on Introduction to Containers and Docker!. The objective of this workshop is to demystify what containers are and how to work with them.</p>\n<p>Purpose of this Workshop is to explain</p>\n<ul>\n<li>History and Basics of Virtualization</li>\n<li>Containers Introduction</li>\n<li>Container terminologies and jargons. Broad overview of containers ecosystem.</li>\n<li>Docker basics</li>\n<li>How to run and manage containers</li>\n<li>Containerize NodeJS application</li>\n</ul>\n<h2 id=\"who-are-you-\" style=\"position:relative;\"><a href=\"#who-are-you-\" aria-label=\"who are you  permalink\" class=\"anchor before\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" focusable=\"false\" height=\"16\" version=\"1.1\" viewBox=\"0 0 16 16\" width=\"16\"><path fill-rule=\"evenodd\" d=\"M4 9h1v1H4c-1.5 0-3-1.69-3-3.5S2.55 3 4 3h4c1.45 0 3 1.69 3 3.5 0 1.41-.91 2.72-2 3.25V8.59c.58-.45 1-1.27 1-2.09C10 5.22 8.98 4 8 4H4c-.98 0-2 1.22-2 2.5S3 9 4 9zm9-3h-1v1h1c1 0 2 1.22 2 2.5S13.98 12 13 12H9c-.98 0-2-1.22-2-2.5 0-.83.42-1.64 1-2.09V6.25c-1.09.53-2 1.84-2 3.25C6 11.31 7.55 13 9 13h4c1.45 0 3-1.69 3-3.5S14.5 6 13 6z\"></path></svg></a>Who Are You ?</h2>\n<p>This workshop is aimed for people with minimum 1-2 year of experience in software development. You should be familiar with very basics of Linux like how to create a directory and file, how to change directory, etc.</p>\n<p>I will be using MacOS to write code and run containers. If you want to follow along, please install docker on your machine beforehand.</p>\n<h3 id=\"setup-instructions\" style=\"position:relative;\"><a href=\"#setup-instructions\" aria-label=\"setup instructions permalink\" class=\"anchor before\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" focusable=\"false\" height=\"16\" version=\"1.1\" viewBox=\"0 0 16 16\" width=\"16\"><path fill-rule=\"evenodd\" d=\"M4 9h1v1H4c-1.5 0-3-1.69-3-3.5S2.55 3 4 3h4c1.45 0 3 1.69 3 3.5 0 1.41-.91 2.72-2 3.25V8.59c.58-.45 1-1.27 1-2.09C10 5.22 8.98 4 8 4H4c-.98 0-2 1.22-2 2.5S3 9 4 9zm9-3h-1v1h1c1 0 2 1.22 2 2.5S13.98 12 13 12H9c-.98 0-2-1.22-2-2.5 0-.83.42-1.64 1-2.09V6.25c-1.09.53-2 1.84-2 3.25C6 11.31 7.55 13 9 13h4c1.45 0 3-1.69 3-3.5S14.5 6 13 6z\"></path></svg></a>Setup Instructions</h3>\n<ul>\n<li>For Mac: <a href=\"https://www.docker.com/products/docker-desktop\">Docker Desktop Community</a></li>\n<li>For Linux: <a href=\"https://docs.docker.com/engine/install/ubuntu/\">Docker Engine Community</a></li>\n<li>For Windows <a href=\"https://docs.docker.com/docker-for-windows/install/\">Docker Desktop</a></li>\n</ul>\n<p>For Windows user, this <a href=\"https://medium.com/@mbyfieldcameron/docker-on-windows-10-home-edition-c186c538dff3\">blog post</a>\nmight be helpful as well.</p>\n<p>Do note that containers can take lot of CPU and memory. If your machine RAM size is above 8GB, you will be fine. things can slow down on machines with low CPU and RAM capability.\ntrying things along with the workshop can also take a lot of bandwidth because we will download a lot of things. be aware of that.</p>\n<h2 id=\"who-am-i-\" style=\"position:relative;\"><a href=\"#who-am-i-\" aria-label=\"who am i  permalink\" class=\"anchor before\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" focusable=\"false\" height=\"16\" version=\"1.1\" viewBox=\"0 0 16 16\" width=\"16\"><path fill-rule=\"evenodd\" d=\"M4 9h1v1H4c-1.5 0-3-1.69-3-3.5S2.55 3 4 3h4c1.45 0 3 1.69 3 3.5 0 1.41-.91 2.72-2 3.25V8.59c.58-.45 1-1.27 1-2.09C10 5.22 8.98 4 8 4H4c-.98 0-2 1.22-2 2.5S3 9 4 9zm9-3h-1v1h1c1 0 2 1.22 2 2.5S13.98 12 13 12H9c-.98 0-2-1.22-2-2.5 0-.83.42-1.64 1-2.09V6.25c-1.09.53-2 1.84-2 3.25C6 11.31 7.55 13 9 13h4c1.45 0 3-1.69 3-3.5S14.5 6 13 6z\"></path></svg></a>Who Am I ?</h2>\n<p>My name is Satyam Bansal and I'm a Instructor at <a href=\"https://pesto.tech/become-a-developer\">Pesto.tech</a>. I help people become beter software developer. Previous to that I was working with Disney + Hotstar as a Front-end developer.</p>\n<p>catch up with me on Social Media, I would love to hear your stories</p>\n<ul>\n<li><a href=\"https://twitter.com/satyambnsal\">twitter</a></li>\n<li><a href=\"https://www.linkedin.com/in/satyam-bansal/\">linkedin</a></li>\n<li><a href=\"https://satyambnsal.com/\">website</a></li>\n</ul>\n<h2 id=\"where-to-file-issues\" style=\"position:relative;\"><a href=\"#where-to-file-issues\" aria-label=\"where to file issues permalink\" class=\"anchor before\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" focusable=\"false\" height=\"16\" version=\"1.1\" viewBox=\"0 0 16 16\" width=\"16\"><path fill-rule=\"evenodd\" d=\"M4 9h1v1H4c-1.5 0-3-1.69-3-3.5S2.55 3 4 3h4c1.45 0 3 1.69 3 3.5 0 1.41-.91 2.72-2 3.25V8.59c.58-.45 1-1.27 1-2.09C10 5.22 8.98 4 8 4H4c-.98 0-2 1.22-2 2.5S3 9 4 9zm9-3h-1v1h1c1 0 2 1.22 2 2.5S13.98 12 13 12H9c-.98 0-2-1.22-2-2.5 0-.83.42-1.64 1-2.09V6.25c-1.09.53-2 1.84-2 3.25C6 11.31 7.55 13 9 13h4c1.45 0 3-1.69 3-3.5S14.5 6 13 6z\"></path></svg></a>Where to file issues</h2>\n<p>If you find a mistake, I would love to fix it. The best way to do this is to open a pull request or <a href=\"https://github.com/satyambnsal/docker-workshop/issues\">file an issue</a> on the GitHub repo.</p>\n<p>And hey, if you could take a second and <a href=\"https://github.com/satyambnsal/docker-workshop\">star the repo on Github</a> I'd be super appreciative. It helps me reach more people.</p>","frontmatter":{"path":"/intro","title":"Introduction","order":1,"section":"Welcome","description":"Workshop Introduction"}},"allMarkdownRemark":{"edges":[{"node":{"frontmatter":{"order":1,"path":"/intro","title":"Introduction"}}},{"node":{"frontmatter":{"order":2.1,"path":"/virtualization","title":"History of Virtualization"}}},{"node":{"frontmatter":{"order":2.2,"path":"/containers","title":"Containers"}}},{"node":{"frontmatter":{"order":2.3,"path":"/docker","title":"Docker"}}},{"node":{"frontmatter":{"order":3.1,"path":"/docker-ecosystem","title":"Docker Ecosystem"}}},{"node":{"frontmatter":{"order":3.2,"path":"/docker-handson","title":"Docker Handson"}}},{"node":{"frontmatter":{"order":3.3,"path":"/create-docker-image","title":"How to Create Docker Image"}}},{"node":{"frontmatter":{"order":4,"path":"/docker-cheatsheet","title":"Docker Cheatsheet"}}}]}},"pageContext":{}},"staticQueryHashes":["2959687377"]}